Specific Version Pinning: Uses >= to ensure minimum versions while allowing compatibility with newer versions
Core Dependencies: Includes all necessary packages for both CLI and Streamlit interfaces
Analysis Tools: Includes scikit-learn for potential machine learning enhancements
Image Processing: Pillow for image handling in reports

Recommended Installation:

Create a virtual environment:

bash

python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows use `venv\Scripts\activate`

Install requirements:

bash

pip install -r requirements.txt

Optional Additional Packages:

If you want to include PDF report generation with pdfkit, add:
text

pdfkit>=1.0.0

Note: pdfkit requires wkhtmltopdf to be installed on your system separately.

The versions specified are current as of mid-2024 and provide a good balance between stability and access to modern features.
